@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Terms of Use";
    Layout = null;
}
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>@ViewData["Title"] - Cartify</title>
    <style>
        :root {
            --primary-color: #2563eb;
            --primary-hover: #1d4ed8;
            --text-dark: #1e293b;
            --text-medium: #475569;
            --text-light: #64748b;
            --border-color: #e2e8f0;
            --highlight-bg: #f1f5f9;
            --section-spacing: 2.5rem;
            --radius-sm: 0.375rem;
            --radius-md: 0.5rem;
            --shadow-sm: 0 1px 2px 0 rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
            --transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out;
        }

        body {
            font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.7;
            color: var(--text-dark);
            max-width: 900px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 4rem 2rem;
            background-color: #ffffff;
        }

        h1 {
            font-size: 2.25rem;
            font-weight: 700;
            margin: 0 0 0.75rem 0;
            color: var(--text-dark);
            line-height: 1.3;
        }

        .last-updated {
            color: var(--text-medium);
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            margin-bottom: 3rem;
            display: block;
            font-weight: 500;
        }

        .welcome-message {
            font-size: 1.125rem;
            margin-bottom: var(--section-spacing);
            color: var(--text-medium);
        }

        h2 {
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            margin: var(--section-spacing) 0 1.25rem 0;
            color: var(--text-dark);
            position: relative;
            padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
        }

            h2:after {
                content: '';
                position: absolute;
                bottom: 0;
                left: 0;
                width: 3rem;
                height: 3px;
                background: var(--primary-color);
                border-radius: 3px;
            }

        p {
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
            font-size: 1rem;
            color: var(--text-medium);
        }

        strong {
            font-weight: 600;
            color: var(--text-dark);
        }

        .highlight-box {
            background-color: var(--highlight-bg);
            padding: 1.5rem;
            border-radius: var(--radius-md);
            margin: 2rem 0;
            border-left: 4px solid var(--primary-color);
            box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
        }

        ul {
            padding-left: 1.25rem;
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        }

        li {
            margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
            color: var(--text-medium);
            position: relative;
            padding-left: 1.5rem;
        }

            li:before {
                content: '•';
                position: absolute;
                left: 0;
                color: var(--primary-color);
                font-weight: bold;
            }

        a {
            color: var(--primary-color);
            text-decoration: none;
            font-weight: 500;
            transition: var(--transition);
        }

            a:hover {
                color: var(--primary-hover);
                text-decoration: underline;
            }

        .terms-content {
            background: white;
            border-radius: var(--radius-md);
        }

        @@media (max-width: 768px) {
            body

        {
            padding: 2.5rem 1.5rem;
        }

        h1 {
            font-size: 1.875rem;
        }

        h2 {
            font-size: 1.375rem;
        }

        }

        @@media (max-width: 480px) {
            body

        {
            padding: 2rem 1.25rem;
        }

        h1 {
            font-size: 1.75rem;
        }

        h2 {
            font-size: 1.25rem;
        }

        .highlight-box {
            padding: 1.25rem;
        }

        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Cartify Terms of Use</h1>
    <span class="last-updated">Last Update: @DateTime.Now.ToString("MMMM dd, yyyy")</span>

    <p class="welcome-message">Dear users, welcome to Cartify!</p>

    <div class="terms-content">
        <p>
            Cartify products and services are owned and operated by [Your Company Name] (hereinafter referred to as "Cartify" or "we").
            Before using the Services, please make sure to carefully read and understand this "Cartify Terms of Use"
            (hereinafter referred to as "these Terms") as well as other related terms, policies, or guidelines of this platform.
        </p>

        <div class="highlight-box">
            <p>
                When you use a specific function of the Services, there may be separate terms, related business rules, etc ("Specific Terms")
                for that specific function. In the event of any conflict between these Terms and the Specific Terms, the provisions of the
                Specific Terms shall prevail. All the aforementioned terms and rules form an integral part of these Terms (collectively
                referred to as "All Terms"), and have the same legal effect as the main text of these Terms.
            </p>
        </div>

        <p>
            Among them, the <strong>Cartify Open Platform Terms of Service</strong> is specifically applicable to your use of the
            Application Programming Interface (API) or other developer tools and open platform services provided by this platform.
        </p>

        <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
        <p>
            By accessing or using Cartify's services, websites, and applications (collectively, the "Services"), you agree to be bound by these Terms.
            If you do not agree to all of these Terms, you may not use our Services.
        </p>

        <h2>2. Service Description</h2>
        <p>
            Cartify provides [brief description of your services]. We reserve the right to modify or discontinue the Services at any time without notice.
        </p>

        <h2>3. User Responsibilities</h2>
        <p>When using our Services, you agree not to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Violate any laws or regulations</li>
            <li>Infringe on any intellectual property rights</li>
            <li>Upload or transmit harmful or malicious content</li>
            <li>Interfere with or disrupt the Services</li>
            <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to our systems</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Account Security</h2>
        <p>
            You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account credentials and for all activities that occur under your account.
            Notify us immediately of any unauthorized use of your account.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>
            All content included in the Services, such as text, graphics, logos, and software, is the property of Cartify or its licensors and
            protected by intellectual property laws.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Privacy</h2>
        <p>
            Your use of the Services is subject to our Privacy Policy, which explains how we collect, use, and protect your personal information.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
            To the maximum extent permitted by law, Cartify shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages,
            or any loss of profits or revenues.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Modifications to Terms</h2>
        <p>
            We may modify these Terms at any time. We will provide notice of material changes, and your continued use of the Services constitutes acceptance
            of the modified Terms.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Governing Law</h2>
        <p>
            These Terms shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of [Your Jurisdiction], without regard to its conflict of law provisions.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Contact Information</h2>
        <p>
            For questions about these Terms, please contact us at [your contact email].
        </p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
